## Quick start

```bash
./dev               # install uv + just, sync deps, install lefthook
just docs::live     # live-reload preview at http://localhost:8000
```

## Common commands

```bash
just docs::live       # local live-reload preview
just docs::build      # build static site into site/
just docs::validate   # lefthook checks (markdown/spelling/ruff) + clean build
just docker::run      # serve the built site via nginx at http://localhost:8080
just version::bump patch && just version::tag   # cut a release tag
```

## Updating from the template

```bash
just copier::update   # pull the latest copier-docs changes (commit your work first)
```

## CI/CD

{% if ci_platform == 'gitlab' -%}
`.gitlab-ci.yml` runs lint + build on every push/MR, publishes the site to
**GitLab Pages** on `{{ '$CI_DEFAULT_BRANCH' }}`, and pushes an nginx image to
`{{ gitlab_registry }}`. CI jobs are thin wrappers around `just cicd::*`.
{%- else -%}
`.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs lint + build on pushes/PRs and pushes an nginx
image to `{{ github_registry }}` on tags; `.github/workflows/pages.yml` deploys
the site to **GitHub Pages** on the default branch. Workflows are thin wrappers
around `just cicd::*`.
{%- endif %}

## Editing the docs

All content is Markdown under `docs/`. Add new pages to the `nav` table in
`zensical.toml`. The [Showcase](docs/showcase.md) page demonstrates the available
formatting (admonitions, code highlighting, content tabs, card grids, diagrams,
and Markdown includes).
